cs.NI, cs.DC, cs.DS, cs.AR, cs.SE

The paper discusses the architecture and computation offloading in mobile networks, which involves topics related to network infrastructure, distributed computing, data storage, and software engineering. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture), followed by cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing), cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.AR (Hardware Architecture), and cs.SE (Software Engineering).
